{
  "name": "boss",
  "extends": "../soundtrack.json",
  "_comment": "\"The Fallen Captain\" — the dark-knight's personal theme and the FACE of the world's `shadow` motif in music. Distinct from `siege`: siege is the alarm (the whole keep called to the wall, the ember_theme inverted); THIS is one duel with the captain, and it states his OWN leitmotif, shadow_theme, the falling chromatic menace. `approach` stalks in on a low pedal with the theme's head; `duel` churns the full theme over a galloping Dm–Bb–Gm–A7; `onslaught` throws the theme an octave up and inverted so the falling menace CLIMBS — the captain pressing the attack — over a rising pull back to the tonic.",
  "bpm": 132,
  "meaning": "hostile",
  "entity": "the-shadow",

  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "approach",
      "bars": 4,
      "_comment": "The captain stalks in: a low string drone on the tonic, a heavy half-time bass pedal, and just the falling HEAD of shadow_theme low on the brass — dread, not yet violence. A lone kick marks the tread.",
